The paper deals with visual tracking for robotic systems, which is a topic that falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of image-space information and image-space observer, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes an adaptive controller that takes into account uncertain depth information, kinematic and dynamic uncertainties, which are related to control theory (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Lyapunov analysis, which is a common tool in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
